t. In the tradition of feminist autotheory, this collection works outward from the specificity of McGregor’s embodied experience – as a white settler, a fat femme, and a motherless daughter. In so doing, it invites readers to reconsider the culture, media, political structures, and lived experiences that inform how we move through the world separately and together.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFeminism. 0aFeminist theory. 0aFeministszCanadavBiography. 0aPodcasterszCanadavBiography. 0aWomen's studies. 4aFilm & Media. 4aLiterary Criticism. 4aSocial Science: Women’s studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Feminist.2bisacsh  aErin Wunker.  aEugenia Zuroski.  aHil Malatino.  aJenn Shapland.  aKatherine McKittrick.  aKathleen Fitzpatrick.  aKathleen Stewart.  aLauren Berlant.  aMinelle Mahtani.  aSara Ahmed.  aSecret Feminist Agenda.  aTransCare.  aTressie McMillan Cottom.  aWitch, Please.  aasexuality.  aautotheory.  afeminist friendship.  afeminist killjoy.  afeminist podcasting.  afeminist scholarship.  aopen access.  apublic scholarship.  arelatability.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419540uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978177112559840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781771125598423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781771125598/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-127419-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles